OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774455107
OL,3,CTeenager jailed for killing mother
OL,4,Cwith a hammer because of 'hatred of
OL,5,Cwomen'
OL,7,F"Your brother didn't want to leave
OL,8,Fyour mother alone with you in the
OL,9,Fhouse. She had tried to obtain
OL,10,Fassistance for you. You bought a
OL,11,Fnumber of weapons online and went to
OL,12,Fstores to buy them.
OL,14,F"You looked forward to inflicting pain
OL,15,Fand death on your mother. You enjoyed
OL,16,Fwhat you were doing. Exercising
OL,17,Fcontrol over your mother in her final
OL,18,Fhours. Revelling in what you were
OL,19,Fdoing.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G15/17
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46216
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774455107
OL,3,CTeenager jailed for killing mother
OL,4,Cwith a hammer because of 'hatred of
OL,5,Cwomen'
OL,7,F"Callously you ignored her pleas.
OL,8,FInstead managing to persuade her to
OL,9,Fcome with you. Before leaving the
OL,10,Fhouse you made her wear a balaclava
OL,11,Fhelmet.
OL,13,F"She must've been truly terrified in
OL,14,Fthese the last moments of her life.
OL,15,FYou struck her to the back of the
OL,16,Fhead, a number of times. Having killed
OL,17,Fher you dragged her body leaving it in
OL,18,Fundergrowth.
OL,20,F"You boasted on discord about what
OL,21,Fyou'd just done.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G16/17
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46217
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774455107
OL,3,CTeenager jailed for killing mother
OL,4,Cwith a hammer because of 'hatred of
OL,5,Cwomen'
OL,7,F"Your mother's body had been found. In
OL,8,Fbehaving as you did you not only ended
OL,9,Fyour mother's life but caused dreadful
OL,10,Fanguish to the family.
OL,12,F"No sentence I can pass will
OL,13,Fadequately or remotely reflect their
OL,14,Floss or the value of Ms Shellis' life."
OL,16,FRoberts showed no remorse as the
OL,17,Fsentence was passed down.
OL,26,@vD@gO]
